@jmartinm I'm afraid that this is not the right file to paste the loader implementation. You can move it to the state object:

```python
@cached_property
def loader(self):
    """TODO."""
    loader_ = import_string(self.app.config[...])  # or it might be already an instance (see https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-records-rest/blob/master/invenio_records_rest/utils.py#L76-L87)
    if loader_ is None:
        loader_ = json_loader_factory(jsonresolver.JSONResolver(
            plugins=['invenio_jsonschemas.jsonresolver']
        ))
    return loader_
```

Since you only use this with 401 errors, you could do something like:

```
class MockedFailedRequest(object):
    def __init__(self, failure_response):
        self.status_code = 401
        self.failure_response = failure_response

    def json(self):
        return failure_response
```

a function for a multiline one liner is maybe too much? I would suggest to split it in (at least) two like:
```
if resource_id is not None:
    return urljoin(self.get_collection_endpoint(), str(resource_id))
```

By default python returns None. Although I would suggest doing it explicitly just in case...

So something like this?

```
  def package_iterator(self, resolvable, existing=None):
    iterator = Iterator(fetchers=[Fetcher([self.__cache])])
    packages = self.filter_packages_by_interpreter(
        resolvable.compatible(iterator), self._interpreter, self._platform)

    if packages:
      if resolvable.exact:
        return packages

      if self.__cache_ttl:
        packages = self.filter_packages_by_ttl(packages, self.__cache_ttl)
      else:
        packages = []

    return packages + super(CachingResolver, self).package_iterator(resolvable, existing=existing)
```

For reference, the before:
![localhost_8000_user_ 1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7193975/33152854-b8925c20-cf93-11e7-90f9-37b13bd0da70.png)

@jtamiace Changes look good?

One thing I'm worried about is that we **can** do that for the IPython mode, but some codemirror modes do have this pattern:

```
django/django.js:        require("../../addon/mode/overlay"));
dockerfile/dockerfile.js:    mod(require("../../lib/codemirror"), require("../../addon/mode/simple"));
factor/factor.js:    mod(require("../../lib/codemirror"), require("../../addon/mode/simple"));
gfm/gfm.js:    mod(require("../../lib/codemirror"), require("../markdown/markdown"), require("../../addon/mode/overlay"));
handlebars/handlebars.js:    mod(require("../../lib/codemirror"), require("../../addon/mode/simple"), require("../../addon/mode/multiplex"));
htmlembedded/htmlembedded.js:        require("../../addon/mode/multiplex"));
modelica/modelica.js:    mod(require("../../lib/codemirror"));
nsis/nsis.js:    mod(require("../../lib/codemirror"), require("../../addon/mode/simple"));
rst/rst.js:    mod(require("../../lib/codemirror"), require("../python/python"), require("../stex/stex"), require("../../addon/mode/overlay"));
rust/rust.js:    mod(require("../../lib/codemirror"), require("../../addon/mode/simple"));
tornado/tornado.js:        require("../../addon/mode/overlay"));
twig/twig.js:    mod(require("../../lib/codemirror"),  require("../../addon/mode/multiplex"));
vue/vue.js:        require("../../addon/mode/overlay"),
```

So they will likely be broken...

In fact, why don't we change `TextView` to have a new protected attribute (at the bottom of the class), the `inputType`, which for `TextView` is `'text'` and is used in the `render()` method, but the `PasswordView` subclass just sets this to `'password'`. Then the PasswordView just becomes something like:

```typescript
export
class PasswordView extends TextView {
    inputType: string = 'password';
}
```
or something like that.

Again, here how about just inheriting from `TextView`, and doing something like:

```
render() {
    super.render();
    this.textbox.setAttribute('type', 'password');
}
```
and let everything else be inherited?
